pesticide.PPE: Long-sleeved shirt and long pants; Chemical-resistant gloves: barrier laminate, butyl rubber ≥14 mils, neoprene rubber ≥14 mils, nitrile rubber ≥14 mils, polyvinyl chloride (PVC) ≥14 mils, or Viton® ≥14 mils; Shoes plus socks

Active_Ingredients.name: Azoxystrobin
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: strobilurin class of chemistry which disrupts cellular respiration and energy generation

Active_Ingredients.name: Mefenoxam
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: phenylamide class of chemistry which interferes with fungal RNA synthesis

Active_Ingredients.name: Fludioxonil
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: phenylpyrrole class of chemistry which interferes with osmotic signal transduction

Active_Ingredients.name: Sedaxane
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: succinate dehydrogenase inhibitor (SDHI) and carboxamide class of chemistry which disrupts cellular respiration and energy generation

Active_Ingredients.name: Thiabendazole
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: methyl-benzimidazole carbamate class of chemistry which disrupts ß-tubulin assembly in mitosis

Safety_Information.general_Info: Harmful if swallowed, inhaled or absorbed through skin. Avoid breathing vapor or spray mist. Avoid contact with skin, eyes or clothing. Wash thoroughly with soap and water after handling and before eating, drinking, chewing gum, using tobacco or using the toilet. Remove and wash contaminated clothing before reuse.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Call a poison control center or doctor immediately for treatment advice. Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. Do not induce vomiting unless told to do so by a poison control center or doctor. Do not give anything by mouth to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.if_Inhaled: Move person to fresh air. If person is not breathing, call 911 or an ambulance, then give artificial respiration, preferably mouth-to-mouth if possible. Call a poison control center or doctor for further treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: Take off contaminated clothing. Rinse skin immediately with plenty of water for 15-20 minutes. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: Have the product container or label with you when calling a poison control center or doctor, or going for treatment. For 24-Hour Medical Emergency Assistance (Human or Animal) or Chemical Emergency Assistance (Spill, Leak, Fire or Accident) call 1-800-888-8372.

Application_Info.max_applications_per_season: Make no more than 2 plantings of seed treated with Vibrance Cinco per year.
